Background

		Dr. Izak Bencuya, Ph.D., is an Advisor of Luxera, Inc. Dr. Bencuya served as Senior Advisor of Deeya Energy, Inc. Dr. Bencuya served as the Chief Executive Officer of Deeya Energy Inc. He served as Chief Strategy Officer of Fairchild Semiconductor International Inc. since February 17, 2004 and served as its Executive Vice President and General Manager of Functional Power Group until October 19, 2007. He served as Vice President and General Manager, Discrete Products ... Group of Fairchild Semiconductor International Inc. He joined Fairchild Semiconductor in 1994. He has over 25 years of power semiconductor industry experience. He served as Senior Vice President and General Manager, Discrete Products Group since February 2000. He has worked in the semiconductor and electronics field for 27 years. He spent six years as a Director of Power MOSFET Products. Dr. Bencuya began his career at Yale University where he researched ultra thin oxide MOS devices. He also served at GTE Laboratories and Siliconix in various research and management roles. He served as a Director of Exar Corp. from February 12, 2009 to May 12, 2017. He served as Executive Director of Deeya Energy, Inc. He holds 22 patents and has published extensively in the electronics field. He has B.S. in Electrical Engineering from Bogazici University in Istanbul, Turkey, M.S. and Ph.D. in Engineering and Applied Science from Yale University and MBA from the University of California-Berkeley. Dr. Bencuya is Member of the IEEE Electron Device Society.Read Full Background




